In .NET 10, `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was removed because Android deprecated `adjustResize`. The replacement is the **keyboard accelerators / edge-to-edge** approach using `AndroidWindowInsets`.

## Recommended fix

In your page or layout, wrap your content so the bottom input responds to keyboard insets:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ... />
    <Entry Grid.Row="1" Placeholder="Type a message..." />
</Grid>
```

Then in your `MauiProgram.cs` or platform code, opt into edge-to-edge and let the system handle insets:

```csharp
// Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    // Enable edge-to-edge (required for inset-based keyboard handling)
    WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);
}
```

And in your page's code-behind or a behavior, apply the keyboard inset padding:

```csharp
#if ANDROID
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

// In your page/view setup:
ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
    Platform.CurrentActivity.Window.DecorView, 
    new InsetsListener(yourBottomLayout));

class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    private readonly View _target;
    public InsetsListener(View target) => _target = target;

    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        _target.Padding = new Thickness(0, 0, 0, imeInsets.Bottom / 
            DeviceDisplay.MainDisplayInfo.Density);
        return insets;
    }
}
#endif
```

## Key points

| .NET 9 | .NET 10+ |
|--------|----------|
| `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` | Edge-to-edge + `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` |

- `adjustResize` is gone at the Android platform level (API 30+).
- The `Ime()` inset type gives you the exact keyboard height.
- Adjust `Padding` or `Margin` on your bottom bar accordingly.
- For iOS, `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (enabled by default) should already handle this—no extra work needed.
